### MONTH NOT CODED AS ORDERED FACTOR: Explicitly test H3 (temporal heterogeneity) with H4 (consistency across thresholds) explicitly incorporated:

```{r}
################################################################################
# PURPOSE:
#   Export month-specific model-predicted values and 95% confidence intervals
#   for the McKenzie temporal H2/H4 analyses across all thresholds.
#
# INPUTS:
#   1) otu_table_collapsed_relative.csv
#   2) guild_table_collapsed.csv
#   3) metadata.csv
#
# OUTPUT:
#   - mckenzie_h2_h4_month_predictions_across_thresholds.csv
#
# LOGIC:
#   1) Rebuild the same sample-level temporal dataset used in the H3/H4 script.
#   2) Refit the same detection and richness models for each guild and threshold.
#   3) For each fitted model, generate month-specific predicted values on the
#      response scale with 95% Wald confidence intervals.
#   4) For mixed models, predictions are made at the population level
#      (random intercept set to zero).
#   5) For fixed-effect fallback models, predictions are averaged equally across
#      nests so that month estimates are adjusted for Nest_ID without being
#      driven by uneven sample counts.
################################################################################

# --------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Libraries
# --------------------------------------------------------------------------

